title: For Sale/Trade:  J. C. HIGGINS 20 GAUGE BOLT-ACTION SHOTGUN MODEL 583.19
postcontent: J. C. HIGGINS 20 GAUGE BOLT-ACTION SHOTGUN MODEL 583.19 Some history: The JC Higgins (Sears) Model 10 The Sears and Roebuck listed the Model 10 bolt-action shotgun in their catalog from 1946 until 1958 and priced it at $30 (you could get a cleaning kit and case for about 45 cents more). It was a “man sized, hard hitting shotgun” according to the catalog. They came in .410, 12, 16 and 20 gauges, had a four-round capacity, and most could be bought with either a modified or full choke barrel. The Model 10 has never been the center of controversy per se, but there was and is an ongoing debate about its history and even its name. Though it’s generally accepted that High Standard, a company most notable for its .22-caliber competitive- and Olympic-quality pistols, manufactured the bulk of the Model 10s, there is still debate on who was originally produced it. Some conjecture that the early ones were made by H&R because H&R sold a bolt-action shotgun at that time that was very similar to it. Also, I’m referring to it as the Model 10 as do most people, but on many of the units you’ll find “583.xx” stamped on the barrel (the last digits denoting slight modifications). The 583.xx is another number Sears used on these guns and others like it, so needless to say it may get confusing. Asking $140 obo. This is a 20 gauge model. Full choke. In good working order. Shows sign of normal wear for its age.  Will need to see IN driver's license and LTCH. Would like to keep transaction to Indianapolis/Zionsville/Carmel area. Thank you for looking.

title: For Sale/Trade:  NightForce ATACR 5x25x56

postcontent: I have for sale a NF ATACR 5x25x56 Mil/Mil with the tremor 3 reticle and a 34mm main tube.  This is an amazing optic.  I have had it out to an indoor rifle range twice and a camping outing once.  Mounted on an AR10.  The tremor 3 reticle is superb for ranging as well as follow up shots and having the ability to make advanced holds without dialing turrets.  The reticle is what really steps up the price on this optic.  The tremor 3 also provides leads for moving targets from 2mph to 60mph as well as wind holds for 5, 10, 15, 20 mph winds.  It comes with tenebrex flip caps with the NF logo on them.  It is a zero stop model.  It is not illuminated as they cant illuminate a First Focal Plane Tremor 3.  The 56mm objective transmits a great amount of light even in low light conditions.  If you have any other questions don't be shy.  I am not in a hurry to sell and the price is firm at $3100.  This is $300 cheaper than new without shipping.  I guarentee you will not find a single scratch or scuff on this optic.  I may be open to trades for other optics plus cash.  Will ship insured on your dime.
